The below sounds like a bug (Maybe some of the other fellas from here at 
the Archive have an opinion on).   Sounds like your value of zero for 
max-trans-hops is stopping prerequisites being crawled (Codes like -63 
are defined on end of user manual).

You might try moving off the PathScope and instead use preferred 
DecidingScope.   This scope allows addition of &#39;rules&#39; regards how each 
URL is evaluated scope-wise.  Gives more fine-grained control.  There 
are a large set of &#39;rules&#39; to choose from including a &#39;fetch prereqs 
whatever the rules above me say&#39;.  You can pick up the DecidingScope 
configured with defaults -- a good place to start -- by selecting 
&#39;deciding-default&#39; when creating a job based on a profile (Since release 
of 1.8.0, the deciding-default has become the &#39;default&#39;).

Might get you over the above issue -- or create it in a new context.  If 
the latter, we need to fix it.

Thanks,
St.Ack


